Preliminary: MCMC

Building MCMC function

MCMC = function(target, r.trans, d.trans, n.simu, x.0){
  x = matrix(, nrow = length(x.0), ncol = n.simu)
  x.c = x.0
  for (i in 1:n.simu){
    x.p = r.trans(x.c)
    u = runif(1)
    alpha = (target(x.p)*d.trans(x.p, x.c))/(target(x.c)*d.trans(x.c, x.p))
    if (u<alpha){
      x.c = x.p
    }
    x[,i] = x.c
  }
  return(x)
}

Testing MCMC

test.target = function(x){
  return(dnorm(x, mean=1, sd=2))
}

test.r.trans = function(x){
  return(rnorm(1, mean=x, sd=1))
}

test.d.trans = function(x,y){
  return(dnorm(y, mean=x, sd=1))
}

set.seed(1234)
n.simu=10^4
x.0=0
simu = MCMC(test.target, test.r.trans, test.d.trans, n.simu, x.0)

plot(0:100, c(x.0,simu[1,1:100]))

acf(simu[1,1:100])

step=50
simu.sub = simu[step*(1:floor(n.simu/step))]
hist(simu.sub)

print(mean(simu.sub))
## [1] 1.126688
print(sd(simu.sub))
## [1] 1.99562

test.target = function(x){
  dist = nndist(x, rep(0,length(x)))
  ans = 0
  if (min(dist)>=0.1){
    ans =1
  }
  return(ans)
}

Problem 1: Grab one and alternate

test.r.trans = function(x){
  select = floor(runif(1)*9)+1
  ans = x
  ans[select] = runif(1)
  return(ans)
}

  ans = ans - floor(ans)

Alternative Way: Gibbs Sampling

Gibbs = function(target, r.trans, n.simu, x.0){
  dim = length(x.0)
  x = matrix(, nrow = dim, ncol = n.simu)
  x.c = x.0
  for (i in 1:n.simu){
    for (d in 1:dim){
      x.p = r.trans(x.c, d)
      x.c = x.p
    }
    x[,i] = x.c
  }
  return(x)
}

Testing Gibbs

Problem 1: Gibbs versino

test.r.trans = function(x,d){
  a=0
  if (d > 1){
    a = x[d-1]+0.1
  }
  b=1
  if (d < 9){
    b = x[d+1]-0.1
  }
  ans = x
  ans[d] = runif(1)*(b-a)+a
  return(ans)
}

set.seed(1234)
n.simu=10^5
x.0=t(0.11*(1:9))
simu = Gibbs(test.target, test.r.trans, n.simu, x.0)
plot(1:n.simu, simu[1,])

acf(simu[1,], lag.max = 1000)

step=50
simu.sub = simu[1,step*(1:floor(n.simu/step))]
hist(simu.sub)
